<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-NOTEBOOK-SCHOENFELD-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OFFENSIVE LINE COACH KEEPS 49ERS ON TRACK 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVE SCHOENFELD  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   They have enough ex-Cardinals to start an alumni chapter.
</P>
<P>
   Running back  &UR; Garrison Hearst, strong safety  &UR; Tim McDonald and
left guard  &UR; Ray
 &UR; Brown are starters for the San Francisco 49ers.  &UR; Chuck Levy is the
team's return specialist and backup running back.  &UR; Randy Kirk is
the deep snapper.
 &UR; Chad Fann is the No. 3 tight end.
</P>
<P>
   Only McDonald went to the 49ers' in a free-agent bidding war.
Hearst, Levy, Brown and Fann were cut. Kirk is with his sixth team.
</P>
<P>
   So who said the 49ers were the best team owner  &UR; Eddie DeBartolo
Jr.'s money can buy?
</P>
<P>
   The perennial NFC West champions have gained 500 yards on the
ground in their first two games using a starting line that includes
two tackles who weren't drafted, two guards who were taken in the
eighth round (there isn't an eighth round anymore) and a center who
was a sixth-round choice.
</P>
<P>
   Maybe the credit should go to offensive line coach  &UR; Bobb
McKittrick, the only person in the 49ers' organization who has held
the same job since  &UR; Bill Walsh took over as coach in 1989.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's the smartest coach in football,'' said Oakland Raiders
Coach  &UR; Jon
 &UR; Gruden, a former 49ers assistant.
</P>
<P>
   He's also one of the strangest.
</P>
<P>
   McKittrick, who will be 63 in December, won't wear a coat, even
if the team is playing in Buffalo in December.
</P>
<P>
   After a game in freezing rain in Chicago during the 1980s, Walsh
had a team doctor talk to McKittrick about his health.
</P>
<P>
   Green Bay Packers Coach  &UR; Mike
 &UR; Holmgren, a former 49ers offensive coordinator, said he once tried
to communicate from the press box with McKittrick, who was on the
sidelines. But McKittrick was so cold, Holmgren couldn't understand
him.
</P>
<P>
   ``I said, `Bobb, you've got to put on a jacket,' '' Holmgren
said. ``His teeth were chattering,'' Holmgren said. ``I was looking
at it from a pretty practical standpoint. He could be out there
naked if he could tell me what (plays) he wanted to do running the
ball.''
</P>
<P>
   McKittrick said he just doesn't get as cold as most people.
</P>
<P>
   ``I became like &UR; Woody Hayes,'' McKittrick said. ``I got the
reputation, and I enjoyed it. You can't get much reputation as an
offensive line coach. You're pretty anonymous. So, I just didn't
wear (a coat), and it wasn't bad. But other people thought I was
colder than I was.'' &QL; 
Dumb and dumber
</P>
<P>
   St. Louis Rams Coach  &UR; Dick Vermeil was willing to overlook
running back
 &UR; Lawrence Phillips' three arrests and the 23 days he served in jail
to consider re-signing him last week.
</P>
<P>
   But team officials stopped it, telling Vermeil they were
dead-set against it.
</P>
<P>
   The Rams also received numerous phone calls from fans
complaining that the team was even considering the move.
</P>
<P>
   ``I understand it has created quite a little news thing around
the country,'' Vermeil said. ``I'm sorry I did that. I'm going to
have to start not answering questions honestly when someone asks me
something because it just creates problems. . . . I get ridiculed.
</P>
<P>
   ``But I like Lawrence Phillips, and I cared about the kid, and I
still do. I recommended him to three other teams. And I couldn't
very well recommend him to three other teams without at least
having him on my mind in some way or another, just as a person, as
a player and a guy that I coached.'' &QL; 
Capital punishment
</P>
<P>
   Denver Broncos quarterback
 &UR; John Elway has few fond memories of the nation's capital.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a bad place,'' Elway said. ``Just ask  &UR; Bill ( &UR; Clinton).''
</P>
<P>
   In 1989, Elway missed the Broncos' Monday night game in
Washington after becoming ill from eating chipped beef on toast at
the White House.
</P>
<P>
   Last June, Elway bypassed the team's Super Bowl-champion visit
to the White House to have a magnetic resonance imaging on his
knee.
</P>
<P>
   Now, Elway might miss today's game against the Redskins because
of a hamstring injury. &QL; 
Streak continues
</P>
<P>
   It has been 26 years since the Broncos last returned a kickoff
for touchdown, the longest streak in the league.
</P>
<P>
   The last Denver player to do so was  &UR; Randy Montgomery, who had a
94-yard score against San Diego on Sept. 24, 1972.
</P>
<P>
   Broncos returner  &UR; Vaughn Hebron said the team became almost
obsessed with scoring on a kickoff last season.
</P>
<P>
   ``It became a joke,'' he said. ``But at the same time, that's
what I look forward to. We're so explosive. If we can take away
half the field, the defense has problems.'' &QL; 
Good aim
</P>
<P>
   When former Washington State quarterback  &UR; Ryan Leaf got mad at a
Spokane, Wash., reporter three years ago, he fired a pass over the
reporter's head at a practice.
</P>
<P>
   Last Monday, he swore at ``San Diego Union-Tribune'' reporter
 &UR; Jay Posner after earlier in the day throwing a pass in practice
that just missed Posner.
</P>
<P>
   The reporter was probably lucky Leaf was coming off a 1-for-15
passing performance the previous day in a loss at Kansas City. &QL; 
Down and out
</P>
<P>
   How far have things fallen in Carolina, which reached the NFC
title game two years ago?
</P>
<P>
   The team (0-2) has gone from the model expansion franchise to
team owner
 &UR; Jerry Richardson calling an impromptu meeting in which he lashed
out at the players and coaches.
</P>
<P>
   A visibly upset Richardson told the team he had spent too much
money in free agency during the off-season to accept such poor
performances.
</P>
<P>
   Some players were stunned by Richardson's actions and considered
his behavior ``inappropriate.'' But apparently they got the
message.
</P>
<P>
   Linebacker  &UR; Jeff Brady called today's game against NFC champion
Green Bay a ``must win.''
</P>
<P>
   ``If you don't think it is, you're crazy,'' he said. ``I don't
care who's coming in here. If any of the guys around here think
it's not urgent, they must not be opening up their eyes.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's a lot of disappointment. We need to play meaner.'' &QL; 
Quick kicks
</P>
<P>
   The Minnesota Vikings haven't lost a game since San Antonio car
dealer  &UR; Red
 &UR; McCombs brought the team over the summer. McCombs even hollered,
``Seven-and-oh,'' as the players walked into the locker room last
week. The Vikings won all four preseason games and are 3-0 in the
regular season.
</P>
<P>
   Miami has allowed only 22 points, tied for the fewest allowed by
a Dolphins team in the first three games.
</P>
<P>
   Former Arizona State defensive lineman  &UR; Dan Saleaumua, now of
the Seattle Seahawks, on his high school in National City, Calif.,
naming its stadium after Olympian  &UR; Gail Devers: ``A couple gold
medals, big deal. Just name the track after her. They named the
whole football stadium after her. So they said they were going to
name the weight room after me. I like that better.'' &QL; 
Includes information from other media sources. Steve Schoenfeld can
be reached at 602-444-8334 or at steve.schoenfeld(at)pni.com via
e-mail. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
