<P>
   11. WE ARE OUR MOTHERS' DAUGHTERS, by Cokie Roberts.
</P>
<P>
   (Morrow, $19.95.) The television news anchor's personal
</P>
<P>
   reflections on women in politics and business, and as mothers,
</P>
<P>
   wives, sisters, and friends.
</P>
<P>
   12.(x) THE PROFESSOR AND THE MADMAN, by Simon Winchester.
</P>
<P>
   (HarperCollins, $22.) How an American who was a certified
</P>
<P>
   lunatic and a murderer helped James Murray compile the
</P>
<P>
   Oxford English Dictionary.
</P>
<P>
   13.(x) THE GIFTS OF THE JEWS, by Thomas Cahill.
</P>
<P>
   (Talese/Doubleday, $23.50.) What Western civilization
</P>
<P>
   owes an ancient nomadic tribe.
</P>
<P>
   14.(x) DIANA: Portrait of a Princess, by Jayne Fincher
</P>
<P>
   and Judy Wade. (Callaway/Simon &AMP; Schuster, $35.) More
</P>
<P>
   than 500 photographs of the Princess of Wales.
</P>
<P>
   15.(x) I AM JACKIE CHAN, by Jackie Chan with Jeff Yang.
</P>
<P>
   (Ballantine, $24.95.) From child of refugees in Hong Kong
</P>
<P>
   to movie star in Hollywood: an autobiography.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ADVICE, HOW-TO, AND MISCELLANEOUS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   1. THE 9 STEPS TO FINANCIAL FREEDOM, by Suze
</P>
<P>
   Orman. (Crown, $23.) How to manage your money. (b)
</P>
<P>
   2. IF LIFE IS A GAME, THESE ARE THE RULES, by Cherie
</P>
<P>
   Carter-Scott. (Broadway, $15.) Ways to achieve a
</P>
<P>
   fulfilling life. (b)
</P>
