   HURRICANE GEORGES
</P>
<P>
   CANE _ Hurricane Georges, a category 3 storm, hits Mobile, but
feeder bands slam the Panhandle with hurricane force winds.
(Elmore, Palm Beach Post). With tracking map.
</P>
<P>
   KEYS _ KEY WEST, Fla. _ Anxious residents are let back through
the roadblock at 1 p.m. today to Key West. What will they find?
(Jenny Staletovich and Scott Hiaasen, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   GEORGES _ PENSACOLA, FLA. _ Main bar on Hurricane Georges.
(Burritt, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   DOMINICAN-SOSA _ SANTO DOMINGO, Dominican Republic _ It's the
final day of the MLB regular season. And the one ray of light in
the darkness for these people -- Chicago Cubs slugger Sammy Sosa --
will make his final assault for the year on the MLB single-season
homerun record today. St. Louis Cardinals first baseman Mark
McGwire upped the ante with two homeruns on Saturday to bring his
total to 68 -- to Sosa's 66. We make our way to his hometown to
watch the game with his biggest fans. (Lipman, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Expected to move in both the (i) International and (s)
Sports catgories by 6:30 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   RIDERS _ WASHINGTON _ In what has become an annual congressional
struggle, Democrats and Republicans, environmentalists and
regulated interests are going down to the wire over ``riders'' that
have been attached to the Interior Department's appropriation for
next year. These amendments would weaken or at least change various
existing environmental laws. Environmental groups hate them and
President Clinton has promised to veto them, with support among
most congressional Democrats and a few Republicans. With fiscal
1999 beginning Thursday, a Clinton veto over environmental riders
could end up shutting down the government, or much of it. (Nesmith,
Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   RIDERBOX _ WASHINGTON _ Listing appropriations bill amendments
and what they do.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   EXODUS _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ The local angle on the national
movement to ``reform'' gays. (Moffett, Palm Beach Post). 45.
</P>
<P>
   JESSE _ Jesse Jackson ends his 13-day Appalachian tour with a
march at Hocking College in Nelsonville, Athens County. this
continues Jackson's reaching out _ and connecting with _
Appalachian America, and sets up a economic roundtable in
Nelsonville on Monday. (Lyles, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
