<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    LSU hopes Dogs have less offense
 &HT;    By Mark Schlabach
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATHENS, Ga. _ Georgia will get a taste of Saturday Night Live
when the Bulldogs travel to Baton Rouge to face sixth-ranked LSU
this week.
</P>
<P>
   Because CBS Sports selected Saturday's Auburn-Tennessee contest
to broadcast at 3:30 p.m., ESPN picked up the Georgia-LSU game,
which will start at 7 p.m. Since 1960, LSU has a record of 165-51-4
in night games at Tiger Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   After watching Idaho gain more than 400 yards offense against
the Tigers, LSU coach Gerry DiNardo is hoping Georgia's offense
won't have nearly as much bite.
</P>
<P>
   The Tigers improved to 3-0 with a 53-20 homecoming win over
Idaho on Saturday, but LSU surrendered 410 yards, including 192
rushing yards on 43 attempts. The Tigers also lost three of four
fumbles, had an extra-point attempt blocked and botched a snap on a
kick attempt.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm glad that we won, and the team should be glad that we
won,'' DiNardo said. ``But there's no way that we're ready to play
six straight SEC games right now. We have a lot of work to do this
week. We didn't play real well on defense at all. We'll struggle
the next six weeks if we play like that.''
</P>
<P>
   LSU tailback Kevin Faulk set a school record with 268
all-purpose yards and four touchdowns against the Vandals, giving
him 5,397 all-purpose yards in his brilliant career. Faulk had 178
yards rushing, 50 receiving and 40 in returns against Idaho. His
rushing yards came on only 13 carries.
</P>
<P>
   Quarterback Herb Tyler is the nation's eighth-ranked passer,
throwing for 551 yards and six touchdowns on 40-of-59 passing.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's really criticial that we tackle well playing against a
back like Faulk and a mobile quarterback like (Tyler),'' Georgia
coach Jim Donnan said. ``The only way you can do that is to have
more contact in practice. You couldn't do it in a game week, but we
were able to do it with the off-week.''
</P>
<P>
   Tyler is the nation's eighth-ranked passer, throwing for 551
yards and six touchdowns on 40-of-59 passing.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
