<P>
   TOP
</P>
<P>
   Lead story:
</P>
<P>
   GERMANY-VOTE (Bonn, Germany) _ On Sunday, Gerhard Schroeder, a
Social Democrat, defeated Helmut Kohl to become German chancellor,
ending an era in Germany and opening a new one in Europe where
center-left governments now dominate the continent's politics. By
Roger Cohen.
</P>
