<HEADLINE>
FRIEND OF RABIN'S ASSASSIN IS SENTENCED 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   JERUSALEM _ A friend of Yigal Amir, the assassin who gunned down
Prime Minister Yitzhak Rabin three years ago, was sentenced Sunday
to nine months in prison for failing to prevent the slaying.
</P>
<P>
   The friend, Margalit Har-Shefi, 23, stood silently eyes as the
sentence was pronounced. Her lawyer said he would appeal.
</P>
<P>
   In imposing the sentence, Judge Nira Lidski said that had Ms.
Har-Shefi ``taken reasonable measures to prevent the crime, this
despicable murder might never have been committed.''
</P>
<P>
   Ms. Har-Shefi, who attended law school with Amir, was convicted
three months ago of failing to report Amir's warnings that he would
kill Rabin.
</P>
<P>
   Ms. Har-Shefi on Sunday described Amir's threat as ``sounding so
imaginary and so unrealistic then'' that she did not believe it. &QL;
</P>
